	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Mrch 13&#44; 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. I. M Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">In answer to yours of yesterday<lb/> I enclose the 2 following copies of receipts of yours<lb/> which will fully agree with my statement</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am aware that we settled up to <date>March 1860</date><lb/> but in your letter &#40;Copy No I&#41; you will perceive that<lb/> on <date>Jan&#44; 15 1861</date> you acknowledge receipt for payment&#59;<lb/> and again in your letter No 2 dated <date>August 14 1861</date><lb/> you again acknowledge receipt&#44; which agrees<lb/> with the entries in my book.  I trust you<lb/> will rectify your mistake.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I enclose also &#36;3.00 for the insertions&#44; which<lb/> will now settle all your claims on me.  As soon as<lb/> I shall be in <placeName>Paris</placeName> I will inform you concern<lb/>ing the subscription for the future&#44; for the present I<lb/> wish to make no engagement.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have yet 3 Bibles and one <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> on hand which I will take with me&#44; as you<lb/> proposed and try to sell them for you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Thanking you heartily for your kind wishes</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Believe me my dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">A Loewe</persName></p>
				<p>Excuse the scribble&#44; in haste.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin.">Please write me an answer</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd. I. M. Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p><placeName>1227</placeName></p>
				<p><placeName>Walnut</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Str</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
